It is the 55th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Teishi|ja|丁巳}} and followed by {{ill|Kihitsu|ja|己未}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Bo|ja|戊|1=Tsuchinoe (戊)}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Horse|ja|午}} represents yang {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生}}, i.e. Fire generates Earth).

== 戊午の年 ==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 58 when divided by 60 is a year of Bokugo ({{ill|year|ja|年}}).
