{{infobox Chinese|l=Yang Earth Horse|kanji=戊午|romaji=tsuchinoe uma|onyomi=bogo|p=wùwǔ|w=wu-wu|mi=u⁵⁵ u²¹|y=mou6 ng5|j=mou6 ng5|ci=mɐu ŋo|mc=məu ŋo|oc-bs=mə ŋaʔ}}
{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}



'''Yang Earth Horse also known as 戊午''' (tsuchinoeuma, bodonouma, bogo) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}.

It is the 55th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支}}, preceded by {{ill|Teishi|ja|丁巳}} and followed by {{ill|Kihitsu|ja|己未}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干}} symbol {{ill|Bo|ja|戊|1=Tsuchinoe (戊)}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支}} symbol {{ill|Horse|ja|午|1=Horse (zodiac)|lt=Horse (午)}} represents yang {{ill|Fire|ja|火}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生}}, i.e. Fire generates Earth).

== 戊午の年 ==
A year in the {{ill|Western calendar|ja|西暦}} that leaves a remainder of 58 when divided by 60 is a year of Bokugo ({{ill|year|ja|年}}).
