{{Sexagenary cycle comprehensive}}
'''Yang Earth Horse also known as 戊午''' (tsuchinoeuma, bodonouma, bogo) is one of the elements of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}.

It is the 55th combination of the {{ill|Sexagenary cycle|ja|六十干支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, preceded by {{ill|Teishi|ja|丁巳|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} and followed by {{ill|Kihitsu|ja|己未|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}. In the framework of {{ill|Yin Yang Five Elements Thought|ja|陰陽五行思想|lt=Yin Yang Five Elements|lt_ja=陰陽五行|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, the {{ill|Heavenly Stems|ja|十干|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Bo|ja|戊|1=Tsuchinoe (戊)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Earth|ja|土|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, while the {{ill|Earthly Branches|ja|十二支|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} symbol {{ill|Horse|ja|午|1=Horse (zodiac)|lt=Horse (午)|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} represents yang {{ill|Fire|ja|火|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, establishing a generating relationship ({{ill|Mutual Generation|ja|相生（そうじょう）|lt=Mutual Generation|lt_ja=相生|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}}, i.e. Fire generates Earth).

